genresAdvancedInfo.name: nz punk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: NZ punk is a raw and energetic style of music that emerged in New Zealand in the late 1970s. It is characterized by fast tempos, aggressive guitar riffs, and lyrics that often deal with social and political issues. NZ punk is known for its DIY ethos and rebellious spirit, and it continues to influence musicians and fans around the world.
